Here are 5 things you can do in the morning to take care of yourself🫶
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our Mindful Nutrition Method students know how important routines and rhythms are! Routines and how we start our day are so important because they have the power to make a positive impact first thing. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Morning routines for me need to have a sense of creativity and space so I intentionally create practices in my morning routine that give me that result — lately it’s been hiking and avoiding the phone.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1 • 📱 instead of waking up and looking directly at your social media or phone, skip! Instead take the time intentionally when you wake up to do a few deep breaths, connect with your body, and set your own intentions for the day before you let others set them for you by looking at social media.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2 • 💦 hydrate with your favorite drink - water, coffee, hot tea, herbal infusions whatever you like.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3 • 🧘 layer your habits: when you’re making coffee or tea in the morning, do a few light stretches to wake your body up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4 • 📓journal, think, or talk about 3 things you’re grateful for. Gratitude isn’t just a practice around the holiday season, it’s a year round practice we all can implement. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5 • 📅planning your day with your top priorities in mind helps you stay on track and when the day is finished you can look at completing those tasks/addressing those top priorities as a big win!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Who said you can’t enjoy greens in your dessert or sweet shake?🌿 

Here’s a delicious way to add fiber and greens to a sweet treat…introducing an updated version of my Green Mint Chocolate Chip Shake!

🍫  What you’ll need to make this:
2 heaping cups of spinach
1 cup @whatiffoods BamNut Milk Everyday
1 cup filtered water (to desired thickness)
2 tablespoons nut butter (or a 1/2 avocado)
1 scoop chocolate plant-based protein powder of choice (I used Four Sigmatic here)
1/4 cup fresh mint (or 1-2 drops of peppermint extract to desired taste)
2 tablespoons of dark chocolate chips (I used Hukitchen here)
1-2 pitted dates (or more if you’d like it sweeter)
½ frozen banana

🌿 How to make this Green Mint Chocolate Chip Shake:
Just add all the ingredients to a high-speed blender and blend until you have the desired consistency and texture you’d like. If you prefer a thicker shake, add ice or reduce the amount of water recommended.

The star ingredient that makes this Green Mint Chocolate Chip Shake (and is the best plant milk for versatile and everyday options) is the BamNut Milk Everyday by @whatiffoods. It’s my go-to when baking, cooking, making smoothies, savory dishes, you name it!

Added bonus to using BamNut Milk is that it has 5g of plant-based protein, contains fiber, is dairy-free, is planet positive, and its main ingredient Bambara groundnut is a legume that fixes nitrogen back into the soil and thereby regenerates degraded lands.

Dates and bananas both contribute to the creaminess of this shake and the sweetness, so those can be adjusted as well.

Enjoy!

The insight you gather from both your wins and learning lessons is what makes you more aware and aligned when you’re thinking about your future goals. 

So, can you do this reflection today?

• What skills and insight did you learn about the goals you achieved and the goals not yet achieved?

• What characteristics of yourself did you build this year?

Let me know what comes up for you!

½ cucumber, thinly sliced
1 tablespoon rice vinegar 
Sprinkle sesame seeds
Bok choy, lightly steamed

🌱 For the sauce:
Sweet Hot seasoning packets included
2-4 tablespoons boiling water
1 tablespoon chili crisp
2 tablespoons creamy salted peanut butter
1 teaspoon sriracha 
Optional garnishes include ½ tablespoon of sesame seeds and fresh green onions.

🌱 Here’s how to make this:
Start by cooking the BamNut noodles according to the package instructions (except do not add the seasoning packets at this stage, just water to cook the noodles).

Take the seasoning and oil packets included in the BamNut Noodle package and add them to a bowl with all the “sauce” ingredients. Stir until creamy. Adjust the hot water in this step to your desired consistency.

The star ingredient in this recipe are the @whatiffoods Bamnut Noodles which contain 6g of fiber and 17g of plant-based protein (from the regenerative crop Bambara groundnut). I really enjoy these noodle packets because they’re so convenient and allow me to make a quick, delicious, and balanced meal in under 10 minutes!

Do you find it challenging to trust your body and listen to your hunger cues? 🌿

If so, you’re not alone! This is especially common in people who have been stuck in the dieting cycle for years.

When we’re constantly following someone else’s rules, it gets pretty difficult to discern what our own body truly wants or needs. 

Our bodies are built to communicate with us, to tell us what we like or dislike, and tell us when we’re hungry or when we’re full. But diets tell us otherwise.

They tell us we’re supposed to eat a certain number of meals per day that contain a specific number of calories that can only be eaten at certain times. Cue the confusion! 

New clients almost never know what true hunger or satiety feels like. They’re almost always struggling to simply understand what they enjoy versus what they believe they, “should” be eating. 

This is another example of a disadvantage to dieting. When we have a balanced, sustainable relationship with food, we work with the body and its cues, not against it. Diets, on the other hand, will tell you to fight those cues and ignore them. 

I know getting started feels like such a challenge if you’re stuck on the first step, so let me help out! 

I made a fun quiz for you: in this free 45-second quiz, you’ll find out your Balanced Eating Archetype, get guidance on what you need to maintain balance and feel good in your body, and learn how to start feeling more confident and at peace with food!

Find Your Eating Type in less than 1 minute! Link in bio @nutritionstripped to take it and then send me a DM with your type!

Which one do you say more often? 

These are just a few examples of what it might sound like being in an all-in or all-out mentality with food.

For some, this may look like trying to eat super “clean” and avoiding all of the “bad” foods. And for others, it may feel like eating anything without being mindful of their nutritional needs. 

My philosophy of balanced eating is pretty simple: eat what your body needs for nourishment and what you want for enjoyment. It takes practice, the right tools, and systems, but once you practice this method, you’ll feel more confident, balanced, and at peace with food! 

By embracing that area right in the middle — where you’re nourishing yourself well and also having space to experience joy around your food experience — you’ll feel better from having this balance.

You’ll have more peace because food won’t be controlling your thoughts, and you won’t need to have that all in or all out mentality. 

If this is a struggle for you, I get it! 

That’s why I create so many free resources, recipes, and experiences for you to engage with to support your food journey. 

My most popular this month has been the Free Class where I teach you in 45-minutes the 3-part Method To Be Confident, Balanced, & At Peace With Food. You’ll learn the #1 habit that's keeping you stuck and stressed with food — find your balanced weight, enjoy food fully, and feel confident!

6 loving kindness food statements to try — which one resonates with you today? 🫶

1. May I feel nourished and satisfied by the food I eat, embracing its power to fuel and support my body and mind.

2. May I be surrounded by a positive relationship with food, allowing myself to enjoy all its flavors and textures without judgment or guilt.

3. May I know the value of mindful eating, appreciating each bite and being present in the moment, connecting with my body’s needs and signals.

4. May I experience peace with food, letting go of negative thoughts or feelings, and embracing food as a source of joy and sustenance.

5. May I be free from the constraints of dieting, understanding that my self-worth is not defined by a number on a scale or a particular food choice.

6. May I feel supported in my journey towards a balanced, compassionate, and joyful relationship with food, knowing that each day is a new opportunity for growth and self-care.

Part of being balanced with food is practicing mindfulness, it’s a core pillar and the foundation of my Mindful Nutrition Method. Mindfulness allows us to experience our current journey with food and loving kindness adds an extra layer of wishing ourselves well with this journey. Do you mindlessly eat?🙋
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Mindful eating is the practice of paying attention to the present moment and being fully present while eating. This includes paying attention to the sensory experiences of food, such as taste, texture, and smell. It also involves being aware of our physical and emotional states while eating, including hunger and fullness cues, as well as any emotional triggers that may influence our eating behaviors.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When we mindlessly eat, it feels like you're disconnected from both why and how you're eating, which leads you to make food choices passively or not as intentional. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This can lead to overeating, not giving your body the nourishment it needs, and even feelings of guilt, which can pull you back into diets in the future.

Here are 5 things you can do in the morning to take care of yourself🫶
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our Mindful Nutrition Method students know how important routines and rhythms are! Routines and how we start our day are so important because they have the power to make a positive impact first thing. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Morning routines for me need to have a sense of creativity and space so I intentionally create practices in my morning routine that give me that result — lately it’s been hiking and avoiding the phone.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1 • 📱 instead of waking up and looking directly at your social media or phone, skip! Instead take the time intentionally when you wake up to do a few deep breaths, connect with your body, and set your own intentions for the day before you let others set them for you by looking at social media.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2 • 💦 hydrate with your favorite drink - water, coffee, hot tea, herbal infusions whatever you like.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3 • 🧘 layer your habits: when you’re making coffee or tea in the morning, do a few light stretches to wake your body up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4 • 📓journal, think, or talk about 3 things you’re grateful for. Gratitude isn’t just a practice around the holiday season, it’s a year round practice we all can implement. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5 • 📅planning your day with your top priorities in mind helps you stay on track and when the day is finished you can look at completing those tasks/addressing those top priorities as a big win!
